<refnamediv><refname>imentropy</refname><refpurpose>Compute image Shannon entropy.</refpurpose></refnamediv>
<refsynopsisdiv><title>Syntax</title><synopsis>value = imentropy(image)
value = imentropy(image, bins)</synopsis></refsynopsisdiv><refsection><title>Parameters</title><variablelist><varlistentry><term>image</term><listitem><para>Input grayscale or RGB image. RGB input is converted to grayscale.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term>bins</term><listitem><para>Number of histogram bins used to estimate entropy. Default is <literal>256</literal>.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term>value</term><listitem><para>Scalar Shannon entropy estimate.</para></listitem></varlistentry></variablelist></refsection>
<refsection><title>Description</title><para><function>imentropy</function> computes base-2 Shannon entropy from the image histogram. RGB input is converted to grayscale.</para></refsection>
<refsection><title>Examples</title><programlisting><![CDATA[image = imread(fullpath(getIPCVpath() + "/images/opencv_fruits.jpg"));
image = imresize(rgb2gray(image), [120 160]);
value = imentropy(image);
disp(value);
imshow(image);]]></programlisting></refsection>
